                            <comment id="14020985" author="tilman" created="Sat, 7 Jun 2014 21:31:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we change something, do you have a test that can show that the change produces something correct?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or can you change it yourself locally and test it? I&apos;d change&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;GregorianCalendar cal = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; GregorianCalendar(1904, 0, 1);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Calendar cal = GregorianCalendar.getInstance(TimeZone.getTimeZone(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;UTC&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
cal.set(1904, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025206" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 14:05:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Working on test case now.  Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025238" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 14:50:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;, I just tested this with and without the modification to TTFDataStream.  It fails on the old code and passes with the new modification.  The only other small change I might add is to set the milliseconds to 0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ttf test document comes from Tika.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025275" author="tilman" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 15:21:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you please attach the ttf file standalone? For some reason, the combined patch doesn&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Update: don&apos;t bother, I found it at TIKA.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025311" author="tilman" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 16:04:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done in rev 1601416 &amp;amp; 1601418 for the trunk and rev 1601417 &amp;amp; 1601419 for the 1.8 version. Thanks for your help!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025321" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 16:12:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you!  Y, that was the first time I&apos;ve built a patch with Eclipse in Windows.  When I create a patch in svn in linux, it won&apos;t let me include binary files.  Is there a preferred way on PDFBox to attach test files?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you, again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025333" author="tilman" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 16:30:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can upload them like you uploaded the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025435" author="hudson" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 17:47:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in tika-trunk-jdk1.7 #36 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/tika-trunk-jdk1.7/36/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/tika-trunk-jdk1.7/36/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1325&quot; title=&quot;Move the font metadata definitions to properties&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-1325&quot;&gt;TIKA-1325&lt;/a&gt;: small workaround until we can integrate &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2122&quot; title=&quot;FontBox&amp;#39;s TTFDataStream doesn&amp;#39;t set timezone in readInternationalDate&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2122&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2122&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Default timezone is now set and then unset for ttf test in FontParsers test. (tallison: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/tika/trunk/?view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1601444&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/tika/trunk/?view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1601444&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
